README.md
Python Game: Adventure Game
This is a simple Python game called Adventure Game. The game is designed to be played on the command line interface.

How to Play
To start the game, navigate to the directory where the game is saved and run the following command:

Copy
python game.py
Follow the instructions on the screen to play the game. The objective of the game is to explore the environment, make choices, and earn points to win the game.

Dependencies
This game requires Python 3.x to run. There are no additional dependencies required to play the game.

Functions
The game uses five functions:

update_score: This function updates the score of the player.
print_pause: This function prints a message and pauses for a few seconds.
knock_on_door: This function is called when the player chooses to knock on the door of the house.
enter_cave: This function is called when the player chooses to enter the cave.
play_game: This function starts the game loop and controls the flow of the game.
Game Loop
The game loop starts when the play_game function is called. The loop continues until the player reaches the maximum score or chooses to quit the game. The loop consists of the following steps:

Print the current score of the player.
Ask the player to make a choice (knock on the door or enter the cave).
Call the corresponding function based on the player's choice.
Check the current score of the player.
If the player has reached the maximum score, print a win message and end the loop.
If the player has not reached the maximum score, repeat the loop.
